This name, whichgives out a genuine Saxon ring, fre- quently occurs in the oldest of the Deeds; and first, in that supposed to be eoeval with the reign of King John. The Herwards were a Family of considerable note in Iveleester‚ in a Century (the 13th) when Iveleester itself was the most im- portant Town in the County. Sucoeeding generations of them became owners also of Estatos iu the adjacent Parishes of Lymyngton and Yevelton. The name appears often and prominently, in the earliest MSS. but at longer intervals in the 14th century. It disappears altogether after 1402. This Family can be traced in direct lineal suecession from King John to Edward III.
